text:
⭐⭐⭐/6 "wolno ci powiedzieć tylko 100 słów dziennie. ponieważ jesteś kobietą" ⚠️ wyobraź sobie świat, w którym zanikają kontakty towarzyskie, wolność słowa, możliwość rozwoju i edukacji, a jedynym pewnym punktem twojej codzienności jest to, że jutro znowu obudzisz się z licznikiem na ręce. będzie on liczył ilość wypowiedzianych przez ciebie słów, by w razie przekroczenia ustalonego przez rząd limitu, dotkliwie porazić cię prądem... będziesz modlić się, by w razie ciąży urodzić chłopca, nie chcąc, by twoja córka musiała przechodzić przez to samo co ty... bo jesteś kobietą.

doktor jean mcclellan poświęciła swoje życie badaniom naukowym. od kiedy amerykański rząd wprowadził nowe reformy w sprawie kobiet, nie może już żyć, jak dawniej. nienawidzi wszystkich mężczyzn, łącznie ze swoimi synami i mężem. pewnego dnia ma możliwość, by uwolnić się od licznika, biorąc udział w badaniach pod czujnym okiem rządu. to dla niej szansa, by mogła odzyskać głos swój i setek innych kobiet. tyle że nie zdaje sobie jeszcze sprawy z tego, że stała się jedynie marionetką rządzących, a ich zamiary nie są tak czyste, jak mogłoby się na początku wydawać. 🤔
.
.
.
"vox" christiny dalcher to książka, która bez wątpienia szokuje, prowokuje i zmusza do refleksji... czy chciałybyśmy żyć w świecie całkowicie podporządkowanym mężczyznom, pozbawione szacunku i jakichkolwiek praw? odarte z godności, zmuszone porzucić pracę, w której się spełniamy i ludzi, z którymi do tej pory często spędzaliśmy czas? myślę, że nie. ja na pewno nie chciałabym żyć w ten sposób.
książkę czytało mi się błyskawicznie, jest napisana prostym językiem (mimo tych rządowych zawiłości), ale pomimo świetnego pomysłu, czegoś mi w niej zabrakło.😔 liczyłam na więcej zaangażowania ze strony głównej bohaterki, tymczasem ona myślała tylko o sobie, córce i swoim kochanku. mimo tego, że sama miałam ochotę przyłożyć jej synowi, to jednak trochę zszokował mnie jej stosunek do niego. książka ciekawa, ale jej potencjał nie został w 100% wykorzystany.
za egzemplarz dziękuję @wydawnictwomuza 😙

stop_filter_tweet: ⭐⭐⭐/6 `` wolno ci powiedzieć tylko 100 słów dziennie . ponieważ jesteś kobietą '' ⚠️ wyobraź sobie świat , w którym zanikają kontakty towarzyskie , wolność słowa , możliwość rozwoju edukacji , jedynym pewnym punktem twojej codzienności jest , że jutro znowu obudzisz się z licznikiem na ręce . będzie liczył ilość wypowiedzianych przez ciebie słów , w razie przekroczenia ustalonego przez rząd limitu , dotkliwie porazić cię prądem ... będziesz modlić się , w razie ciąży urodzić chłopca , nie chcąc , twoja córka musiała przechodzić przez samo co ty ... bo jesteś kobietą . doktor jean mcclellan poświęciła swoje życie badaniom naukowym . od kiedy amerykański rząd wprowadził nowe reformy w sprawie kobiet , nie może już żyć , jak dawniej . nienawidzi wszystkich mężczyzn , łącznie ze swoimi synami mężem . pewnego dnia możliwość , uwolnić się od licznika , biorąc udział w badaniach pod czujnym okiem rządu . dla niej szansa , mogła odzyskać głos swój setek innych kobiet . tyle że nie zdaje sobie jeszcze sprawy z tego , że stała się jedynie marionetką rządzących , ich zamiary nie są tak czyste , jak mogłoby się na początku wydawać . 🤔 . . . `` vox '' christiny dalcher książka , która bez wątpienia szokuje , prowokuje zmusza refleksji ... czy chciałybyśmy żyć w świecie całkowicie podporządkowanym mężczyznom , pozbawione szacunku jakichkolwiek praw ? odae z godności , zmuszone porzucić pracę , w której się spełniamy ludzi , z którymi tej pory często spędzaliśmy czas ? myślę , że nie . ja na pewno nie chciałabym żyć w ten sposób . książkę czytało mi się błyskawicznie , jest napisana prostym językiem ( mimo tych rządowych zawiłości ) , ale pomimo świetnego pomysłu , czegoś mi w niej zabrakło.😔 liczyłam na więcej zaangażowania ze strony głównej bohaterki , tymczasem ona myślała tylko sobie , córce swoim kochanku . mimo tego , że sama miałam ochotę przyłożyć jej synowi , jednak trochę zszokował mnie jej stosunek niego . książka ciekawa , ale jej potencjał nie został w 100 % wykorzystany . za egzemplarz dziękuję 😙

text:
hanyu's famous fs program is "seimei"
it's a program of 2015-2016 & 2017-2018 seasons.
at the beginning of the music hanyu recorded his own breath sound and added it.
this was an idea by hanyu himself.

zenya's sp program music "chopin" in the 2017-2018 season,
she imitated hanyu's idea and recorded and added a breathing sound.

the most disgusting imitation.
if i were imitated the same way from anyone, i would feel very disgusted.

羽生の代表的なfsプログラムとなった「seimei」。
彼の2015-2016/2017-2018シーズンのプログラムである。
曲冒頭に羽生は自らの呼吸音を録音して付け加えた。

zhenyaは2017-2018シーズンのspプログラムの「ショパン」の曲に
羽生のアイディアをそっくり真似して呼吸音を録音して付け加えた。

最も気持ちの悪い後追い真似。
自分が誰かから同じことをされたら、到底我慢できない。

text:
« sa joue a retrouvé le printemps du repos 
ô corps sans poids pose dans un songe de toile 
ciel formé de ses yeux à l'heure des étoiles 
un jeune sang l'habite au couvert de sa peau»
elsa, in les yeux d’elsa, aragon
•
•
la mort de lucrèce, guido cagnacci, vers 1657
•
lucretia, dont la beauté faisait l’unanimité, était encore plus admirée pour sa vertu. le mari de lucrèce festoyait avec le roi tarquin le superbe quand la conversation vint à tomber sur les femmes. pour départager les éloges de chaque mari, un prince proposa de rentrer à rome pour surprendre leurs femmes. ils trouvèrent les princesses autour d’une table dispendieusement garnie tandis que lucrèce, isolée, filait de la laine. sextus tarquin, fils du roi, se mit à la désirer si ardemment qu’il revint quelques jours plus tard pour la violer. humiliée, elle fit jurer son mari et son père de venger son honneur bafoué puis s’enfonça un couteau dans le coeur. brutus, qui accompagnait le père de lucrèce, enjoignit le peuple romain à se révolter contre la tyrannie de tarquin et de ses fils, emportant avec lui la royauté au profit de la république romaine. 
guido canlassi (dit cagnacci), peintre de l’école de bologne, livre ici une demi-figure historique, typique de la deuxième moitié de sa carrière. aux antipodes des codes baroques, la composition épurée concentre le tragique de la scène dans un subtil jeu d’opposition entre le fond intensément noir et le corps à la carnation rayonnante qui s’apprête à être absorbé. cette suggestion de la mort apporte d’autant plus d’intensité que le suicide est imminent. la dague est posée sous le sein, contre la chair, prêt à la percer pour atteindre le coeur. la lame, symbole phallique, rejoue le viol en menaçant de ruiner la féminité de lucrèce. la froideur du métal de la dague s’oppose à la lascivité du corps qui se courbe sensuellement tandis que le visage reflète une jouissance ambiguë avec les yeux clos et la bouche entrouverte. cagnacci signe ici une magnifique toile qui fixe ce moment paroxystique où la douleur rejoint le plaisir, l’érotisme se colore de morbidité, la vie se laisse engloutir par la mort. 
#art #woman #beauty #metoo #history #sensuality #lyon

text: scroll ——->>> steps on how to be an ally for women and girls and to be an advocate for change: 1. when a woman comes to u and tells you about sexual harassment or assault, address it, immediately and thoroughly by hearing her full story and understanding and accepting her truth. 2. help and support that woman decide what actions she wants to take against her aggressor (unless she’s a minor, if you’re a minor and you’re reading this, tell a trusted adult- u can dm me) 3. allow that woman to have the agency to create positive change in the environment in which she was attacked- rules and guidelines that everyone agrees to adhere to. i have been very fortunate to have had little interference with sexual harassment in my career- more-so now that all of the allegations against some of the most heinous perpetrators have been acknowledged. but, of course... #metoo, like every other woman i’ve ever met. i’ve had the privilege of working with some sincerely righteous people, that i’d like to highlight here. @rybovee when i told u about my issues on set, i never anticipated that you would care enough to actually take action. as the director, u had the authority to dismiss my concerns, but instead, u dove in, head first, and you initiated a chain of events that would lead to the making of my “guidelines for a happier healthier tv sex life.” i am so grateful for your acceptance and support and ultimately protection. thank you so much. @theliyah thank you for sitting down with me, for asking me to share my experiences with you, for asking me how i was. how i’ve been doing. for caring. for accepting my guidelines. for being the positive shift that this industry desperately needs. i am so excited for your production company to show the world how things should be done.  #beanadvocate #womensright #guidelines #womenempowerment #supportwomen #positivechange

ifyou're reading this, it's not too late i want to talk to you! or someone you may know!
i’m putting together a small 6 week program dedicated to guiding you through your healing journey allowing you to release trauma and stride in your divine purpose! 
if you want to talk about how i did it 
dm or email: 
beethesage@gmail.com .
.
.
.
we need to talk … just you and me. i know you have stuff to do and i can help you do it!
.
.
.
.
for over 7 years i have served as a youth and community mentor, near-peer holistic wellness coach and academic facilitator. 
i have been a featured artist and speaker at a host of museums, schools, and community programs across the east coast. 
i have been highlighted in local magazines, newspapers, and major educational sites, sharing my passion for holistic wellness, community, environmental preservation, and divine self-expression! .
.
.
.
i’m a b.a. in history with a concentration in afro-diaspora studies!  i served as a founding executive board member of 3 collegiate organizations, one of which was officiated as a non-profit dedicated to providing a space to express authentic black womanhood and examine social injustices and issues from a lens of intersectionality. post graduation i was humbled to be acknowledged by the mayor of my hometown celebrating my service in the community and graduating with honors. i have served as a youth yogi, and creative lead for a faith-based youth leadership academy and i am a certified master level kemetic reiki healer.
.
.
.
.
if you are still reading this, lets get on the phone! 
i only have 4/7 spaces available!
dm @beethesage or email: 
beethesage@gmail.com .
.
.
.
.

we need to talk … just you and me. i know you have stuff to do and i can help you do it!
.
.
.
.
for over 7 years i have served as a youth and community mentor, near-peer holistic wellness coach and academic facilitator. 
i have been a featured aist and speaker at a host of museums, schools, and community programs across the east coast. 
i have been highlighted in local magazines, newspapers, and major educational sites, sharing my passion for holistic wellness, community, environmental preservation, and divine self-expression! .
.
.
.
i’m a b.a. in history with a concentration in afro-diaspora studies!  i served as a founding executive board member of 3 collegiate organizations, one of which was officiated as a non-profit dedicated to providing a space to express authentic black womanhood and examine social injustices and issues from a lens of intersectionality. post graduation i was humbled to be acknowledged by the mayor of my hometown celebrating my service in the community and graduating with honors. i have served as a youth yogi, and creative lead for a faith-based youth leadership academy and i am a ceified master level kemetic reiki healer.
.
.
.
.
if you are still reading this, lets get on the phone! 
i only have 4/7 spaces available!
dm  or email: 
beethesage .
.
.
.

text:
saying no is taking back control of yourself and the situation. .
.
.
there are too many people who wish they had said no but didn't know how too.. well let's start saying it. 
if you don't feel like going out.
.
.
.
if you don't want to be touched.
if you don't want to be involved in a scene. 
if you don't want to play certain games. 
if you don't want to be involved with certain people. 
if you don't want to be hit on. 
if you don't want to eat certain foods. 
if you don't want to go out tonight. 
if you made desicions on an impulse but changed your mind. 
if you don't want to watch something. 
if you don't want to do an activity. 
if you don't want to take part in destructive behaviours.
.
.
.
it's okay to say no. 
if people don't understand, that is their unfortunate problem. 
do not keep doing things because you don't want to upset anyone else. it's not a good enough reason. 
be genuine to yourself. be honest with yourself and your own feelings. 
and when you say yes to things you are actually comfortable with i'm sure you will attract the kind of people you want in your life. .
.
.
peace & good vibes, un_neurotypical.

a self-described #democraticsocialist and a political independent, sanders' campaign brings with it a vast organizing network built during his 2016 campaign that saw him notch wins in key primary states like new hampshire, michigan and wisconsin.”

text:
drumroll please! introducing our #awlcrwanda2019 speakers.
-
macdella cooper
-
macdella cooper @macdella_cooper is a liberian activist and politician who has devoted her lifetime to the empowerment of girls, children and women. having gone through the ordeal of the liberian civil war as a teenager, and fleeing the war-torn zone for exile as a refugee in cote de ivoire, she felt the effect of the war and how conflict affects mostly children and women in the society.
-
she is the founder of the macdella cooper foundation which provides affordable energy, housing and technology in liberia. the foundation is also geared towards empowering disadvantaged youths and children in the society by providing education and basic necessities for the children.
-
read full biography here; https://awlo.org/awlc/speaker/macdella-cooper/

text:
(04/??) like the rest of the world, i was sucked into the viral sensation of roupenian's "cat person," when it was published in the new yorker two years ago. i found the story immensely frustrating for a variety of reasons, but i thought roupenian had successfully tapped into a cultural moment moreso than any other writer i'd seen. she's been pegged as a writer who must be understood in the context of the #metoo era.

throughout these stories, roupenian continues to poke and prod at our culture's sensitivity around sexuality and how our desires can manifest in dismal or disturbing ways. humiliation, violence and sadism are all repeated fetishes that appear across these stories. roupenian shows she's willing to dive deep into the parts of our psyche we'd rather leave unexamined and her willingness to do so is what made this collection worth reading through.

unfortunately, every single one of these stories is ruined by the unavoidable narcissism that exudes out of every thought roupenian commits to page. there is a persistent obsession with extreme idolization, where subjects are humiliated and putdown as they give more and more of themselves to their tormentors. repeatedly, roupenian celebrates these characters' ability to manipulate and abuse everyone around them. it's infuriating.

i'd like to see what roupenian accomplishes in her future, since she's clearly tapped into something unique, but for now — you know you want this reads like the immature doodlings of an egomaniacal prom queen.

1/5 - you know you want this, kristen roupenian

text: "många män kan gå ett helt liv med känslomässiga svårigheter, utan att söka hjälp, men de klarar knappt en månad med erektionsproblem. men det är bra, då finns ju en chans att äntligen sätta ord på både lust och sårbarhet, liksom andra känslor. jag har varit med om situationer där jag har ställt frågan: "hur kändes det då?", och mannen har svarat: "vilka känslor finns det?" förstå, vilket misslyckande för ett samhälle att inte ha lyckats skapa en kultur där varje individ har ett självklart svar på den frågan." läs en nära och intressant intervju med vår författare psykologen calle brunell, aktuell med boken "man – i ljuset av #metoo" i svenska dagbladet. publiceras i tidningen på lördag. länk i bio
name: Brombergs Bokförlag

text:
女人迷獨家專訪在日本#metoo 運動起關鍵作用的記者伊藤詩織。她說，看著台灣前輩走過的路，她對未來有信心。
-
伊藤記得自己首次開記者會那天的情形，「一位我尊敬的記者朋友告訴我，『妳應該穿著如黑色西裝外套般的服裝，人們會比較容易相信你！』」伊藤笑著說，「後來我告訴他，不，我要穿著讓我能感到舒適自在的衣服。」
-
以自己的樣子，正面迎向世界，也足以對社會產生衝擊。「我從未在網路放自己私人照片，但不知怎麼地，許多人透過各種方式、搜尋我朋友的 ｉｇ，找到我的照片，其中一些人找到性侵事件兩個月後，我在工作場合握著相機微笑，人們就說，『你看，性侵兩個月之後，她居然能對著鏡頭笑，她一定是在說謊！』」
-
漸漸她發現，不是鈕扣的問題、也不是能否在工作場合保持微笑的問題，任何一點小事或表現，都可以證成她是說謊的犯人。另一方面，人們對加害者也只有單一想像，任何不符合想像之處，都彷彿能自動證成加害者無罪。
-
「認為被害者或加害者該長什麼樣子、怎麼表現，都是強暴迷思的一環，這也是為什麼我認為需要現身，以我的臉、聲音和名字說話。因為在事件之後，我的人生仍必須持續下去，和其他人一樣。」
-
說出真實，有可能對倖存者造成傷害。例如檢察官一開始就告訴伊藤，如果決定提告，在日本，妳就不必再當記者了。伊藤說，那好吧，我就在別處工作，或做一個自由工作者，「我可以承受失去工作，但我不可以失去我的信念。」
-
文字｜wanyun

text:
¡nosotras sí os creemos!
manda tu historia contándonos el abuso, acoso o maltrato que hayas sufrido y la publicaremos para darte voz de forma anónima.
no podemos publicar nombres de los acusados por problemáticas legales pero sí podemos dar toda la información necesaria para que otras mujeres lo ubiquen y eviten pasar por lo mismo (ciudad, trabajo, amistades, sitios que frecuenta, rasgos físicos, tatuajes, etc.).
seremos tu voz sin que tengas ninguna consecuencia negativa.
¡crearemos entre todas una red de seguridad imbatible!
#yositecreo #autodefensa #metoo #sororidad #noviosdemierda #feminismo #amortoxico

seremos tu voz sin que tengas ninguna consecuencia negativa.
¡crearemos entre todas una red de seguridad imbatible!

text:
one of the highlights of the college art association conference was the feminist art project day of panels on rape, representation, and radicality. it was certainly challenging to hear  the stories behind the activism but at the same time empowering to witness the strong voices on this day (and especially of this date and time) using art as a vehicle to create change, awareness and promote healing through cathartic action. i was especially impressed by #independentcurator @monikafabijanska's presentation "the un-heroic act: representations of rape in contemporary women's art in the u. s." i missed fabijanska's exhibition of the same name in september 2018 so it was a wonderful to hear her thoughts behind the show and see the corresponding publication. her choices of artworks were thoughtful and inclusive, spanning a wide range of materiality. hoping to get a copy before it runs out of print!
#tfap@caa @tfapatrutgers #feministartproject #sexualjustice #contemporaryfeminism #sexualempowerment #intersectionalart #artactivism #artwriter #artcuration #metoo @hyperallergic #metoomovement #monikafabijanska #kimpowerful  #kimpowerwriter #creativeuprising #endviolenceagainstwomen #artexplosion #kapkapow  #caa2019
name: Kim Power

text:
it was this time last year, that i spent a weekend with 4 of the most amazing individuals that grew very quickly to become friend-family for me! @ww flew us all from around the country to nyc to be a part of their annual body issue in #wwmagazine ❤️
talk about #transformation stories... there are none more amazing than the ones i heard from these brave women and men, who overcame sexual abuse, did the healing work and stood with incredible courage to tell their #metoo stories!
it was one of the hardest things we’ve ever done. for such an honor of being in a magazine, it might have been easier if it were only focused on a beautiful before and after... full of weightloss, fashion and feeling beautiful!
but this was deeper and harder work for all of us. it meant having conversations with loved ones and friends who never knew of our abuse. it meant sharing openly with the entire world about the types of things that many will never speak to their significant others or immediate family about!
we did that work! and we felt it reverberate through our lives.
and for that we can be ridiculously proud!!! to @vancesa @jen.may @megankayp and peter on this #transformationtuesday i can’t think of any more amazing inspirations than you!!!
•
•
•

text:
are you ready to be inspired? on this week’s podcast, you’ll be hearing from major nics wetherill (@nicswethrill) and lance sergeant sophie montagne (@mountain_sophie).⁣⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⁣⠀
they are two extraordinary women who are part of the ice maidens — the first all-women team to ski across antarctica using muscle power alone. ⁣⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⁣⠀
“it was over 1700 kilometers which is the equivalent distance of london to venice,” nics shares.⁣⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⁣⠀
in building an all women team, they weren’t trying to prove to men what they can achieve. instead, their aim was to inspire other women of what they can accomplish.⁣⁣⁣⠀
⁣⁣⁣⠀
listen to the episode at the link in my bio to hear about the team’s record-breaking expedition and the message they hope to convey to women with this incredible achievement. ⬆️🎧.⁣⁣⁣⠀
.⁣⁣⁣⠀
.⁣⁣⁣⠀
.⁣⁣⁣⠀
#icemaiden #strongwomen #genderequality #standtogether #feminist #advancewomen #empowerwomen #metoo #timesup #5050by2030 #equalityatwork⁣

text:
jeg føler mig splittet imellem at ville hylde en designer som sæson efter sæson har skabt fantastiske kreationer og shows.
universer jeg så frem til og glædede mig til. holdt modehuse med enormt kultur i live og i nogle sæsoner mere relevante end nogensinde.

og på den anden side tage afstand fra en mand som har udtalt sig, blandt andet: "one cannot — even if there are decades between them — kill millions of jews so you can bring millions of their worst enemies in their place" omkring tysklands immigrations politik. 
eller " ...if you don't want your pants pulled about, don't become a model! join a nunnery..." i forbindelse med #metoo.

så denne lille reflektion, bliver min hyldest til de fantastiske designs, men med et håb om at lagerfelds efterfølger bliver mere næste kærlig og bevidst om de samfund vi lever i.
.
.
.
.
.
#karllagerfeld #seperateartfromartist #dilemma #thoughts

universer jeg så frem til og glædede mig til. holdt modehuse med enormt kultur i live og i nogle sæsoner mere relevante end nogensinde.

eller " ...if you do not want your pants pulled about, do not become a model! join a nunnery..." i forbindelse med etoo.

så denne lille reflektion, bliver min hyldest til de fantastiske designs, men med et håb om at lagerfelds efterfølger bliver mere næste kærlig og bevidst om de samfund vi lever i.

.
.
.

text:
“não se nasce mulher, torna-se mulher.” essa conclusão, de autoria de simone de beauvoir, militante feminista e escritora - autora de o segundo sexo (1949), base para a discussão teórica do feminismo –, embora seja alvo de muitas interpretações distorcidas quanto as intricadas questões de gênero, explicita a figura feminina como uma edificação social e cultural. “a diferença biológica produz uma desigualdade que não é meramente biológica”. a visão social da mulher é projetada a partir da construção de um objeto de dominação masculina. 
na leitura de @djamilaribeiro1 sobre a autora francesa, “a mulher não seria definida em si, na sua originalidade, mas em comparação ao homem e em detrimento dele”. nessa linha, izilda johanson, destaca: “enquanto indivíduo do sexo feminino, significa existir como ser relativo, como outro em relação ao um, o indivíduo do sexo masculino, e sem reciprocidade”. o segundo sexo.
••
e há uma forma de escapar desse cárcere determinista? sim! sempre há! a libertação passa pelo ato de as mulheres reconhecerem-se como sujeitos. na visão de marcia tiburi, “uma mulher frágil desperta o desejo de fragilizar”. a afirmação da força e das potencialidades femininas são as vias para a transformação do pensamento social masculinizado. sintetizando toda essa exposição, beauvoir diria: “se quero definir-me, sou obrigada inicialmente a declarar: ‘sou uma mulher’. essa verdade constitui o fundo sobre o qual se erguerá qualquer outra afirmação”.
••
a revista em destaque é uma edição especial do mês de janeiro, que pode ser adquirida no site da @cultrevista. #nãoépubli 😉😊
••

text:
"violence is literally the enemy of pleasure. if i feel unsafe in my body or if i'm struggling with trauma, i'm being robbed of my right to the pleasure that my body is capable of and that's a really important loss." jaclyn friedman, @jaclynfable at explore more summit 2019
.
here's one thing you won't see talked about in the glossy magazines about fancy sex positions and yoga retreats that sell us on self-care and wellness - that pleasure isn't accessible to everyone because safety is a pre-requisite for pleasure.
.
the science shows (and we inherently know this based on experience, too) that our brains literally interpret stimuli as potential threats when we experience violence and feel unsafe. a soft touch can feel terrible. delicious food can become tasteless or feel like it might kill us. .
before we can get to pleasure, we must always talk about access to safety. and safety looks different to everyone. safety exists on a spectrum. it's not all or nothing, just like pleasure isn't all or nothing. if we can begin to touch into safety in small ways, then often we can begin to touch into pleasure in similar ways.
.
we don't often hear about the loss of pleasure that survivors of sexual violence face (nor the folks experiencing ongoing daily oppression). it's a huge cost in these bodies that are actually built for pleasure. .
let's rage together. let's grieve together. let's explore safety, belonging, pleasure, and connection together. that's what we're doing at the 4th annual explore more summit this year where jaclyn is speaking along with dozens of others.
.
it's free, online, and starts february 25th. grab your spot by signing up at exploremoresummit.com today!
.
#feminist #feminism #exploremoresummit #ems2019 #trauma #survivor #thebodykeepsthescore #metoo #timesup #yesmeansyes #affirmativeconsent #socialjustice #equality #pleasure #relationshipadvice #healing

text:
rant coming!!! this makes me so mad!! #metoo  this movement is so far out in left field it’s pitiful!! not every touch is harassment. not every word is harrassment. 😡
the nurse in that iconic picture was proud to be welcoming home the troups. this iconic statue is historic and you idiots have once again gotten it all wrong. 
you’re offended because some guy is leering at your boobs?  then cover them up!  you’re upset because 30 years ago you had sex with someone who told you they would get you a part??!! then don’t have sex with them!! you’re offended because some guy patted your butt 10 years ago?? you should have done something 10 years ago. this “movement “ takes the focus off of honest, legitimate sexual crimes against women and puts it on stupid, petty ridiculous accusations that can’t even be substantiated!! the shame is on all of you who trivialize real issues, who, after deciding they shouldn’t have slept with that guy (your choice!) have now decide you’ve been harrassed, who wanted the acting part so you did it...you did it, who bare your parts and feel harrassed because someone comments on them. 
me too....take responsibility for your part and get over your bull&@&& issues!. #metoo #metoomovement

text:
carly van liere sees her role as abbey as an opportunity for empathy and a way to connect the audience with the experience of survivors and the possibility for healing and growth. currently, she works as an actor and model in san francisco. she has extensive training, with a bfa in acting from university of michigan and a semester of postdramatic actor training which she completed in berlin, and she continues to train in the bay. she sings, shreds the uke, dresses with style, reviews plays, and does her thang. catch her in rvp’s production of these shining lives, directed by mary ann rodgers, march 2019! donate to support carly in telling abbey’s story at the link in our bio.

text:
feeling like you don't fit in is pretty hard to escape in life. 
there are too many people in this world for it not to happen. 
trying to fit in is like trying to jam a jigsaw piece into the wrong puzzle. 
it’s not going to fit and is probably going to crumple up and become distorted.

take the pressure off yourself. your puzzle is out there waiting for you to slot right in.

every puzzle is made complete. even you.

there is one thing i want you to remember as well... do not focus on people who "look" like they fit in.

often you'll find they are still the wrong piece in the wrong puzzle.

if you put any attention on them you take it off yourself. remember that. 🧩

follow @jamesmalins

text:
i wonder if the 11-year-old boy arrested, suspended and *jailed* for kneeling during the pledge of allegiance at his school knows that songs like this exist. because they exist for him. his bravery. his courage. his right to be his true self in a world that tells him the only viable solution to his gallantry is to go back to africa. rewind to yourself at that age. can you imagine taking on an issue of national debate? i didn’t even have the courage to stand up for myself, let alone the rights of all black and brown people. this kid is a hero. ✊🏿✊🏾✊🏽✊🏼 _____
take heed, contemptuous fools. kids like this are changing the world you so desperately cling to. 
_____
#indiaarie #whatif #blacklivesmatter #blm #standup #speakout #itsuptous #metoo #wematter #youmatter #ourlovecanchangetheworld #filipinxforblacklives #poc #pocpower

text:
the iconic designer @karllagerfeld has passed away. he was one of the most important and prolific designers of his generation.
.
lagerfeld was born in hamburg in 1933 and began his career as pierre balmain’s assistant. during the years he became a fashion icon, founding his own line and working for fendi and chanel. even in his 80s, he was still designing an average of 14 new collections a year. his signature combination of “high fashion and high camp” attracted stars as rihanna, princess charlene of monaco and julianne moore.
.
in his personal life, lagerfeld lived alone with his cat @choupettesdiary, who became as famous as her master. she even had her own maids, diamond necklaces and an instagram account with over 100.000 followers.
.
yet, karl lagerfeld also did make some controversial statements. during the rally of the #metoo movement, people from various industries (also the fashion industry) started supporting the victims and the implementation of new guidelines to prevent assault. lagerfeld, however, started to defend stylist karl templer, who was accused of sexual harassment of models, by stating that “you shouldn’t become a model if you don’t want your pants pulled about.”
.
👉 what do you think of karl lagerfeld?
.
📸 maxppp
.
.
.
#fashion #karllagerfeld #chanel #fendi #designer #metoo

text:
abuse. not just women but men face too. many men are sexually abused everyday. but, we as a society, choose to ignore it because a "man" can never be abused. while women have various platforms to come out openly and share their story of abuse, men are shunned, ridiculed and told they can never be abused. 
as much as we believe women and their #metoo stories, let us believe men and their #metoo stories too.

text:
❝ " le désir masculin est imprévisible " ❞
─
─
📌 ↬ 19/02/2019.
─
↬ début février, un ancien gouverneur sud-coréen, étoile montante de son parti, a été condamné à trois ans et demi de prison pour avoir violé sa secrétaire à plusieurs reprises. cette condamnation intervient alors que, depuis un an, l'essor du mouvement #metoo en corée a encouragé de nombreuses femmes à oser briser le silence pour dénoncer les violences sexuelles.
─
↬ mais dans ce pays encore très patriarcal, le gouvernement ne montre guère l'exemple, comme le montrent ses directives pour les cours officiels d'éducation sexuelle, au contenu incroyablement sexiste. ces cours de l'education nationale assurent qu'il est " naturel pour les hommes de vouloir être remercié pour l'argent qu'ils ont dépensé lors d'un rendez-vous amoureux (…) et qu'en conséquence, des viols peuvent arriver. " ils ont soulevé une immense indignation l'année dernière quand ils ont été rendus publics.
─
↬ la militante et écrivain féministe lee min-kyung, elle, accuse les autorités de présenter comme normales l'obligation de soumission et les violences physiques et morales imposées aux femmes.
─
↬ au-delà de la question du sexisme, les associations pointent un manque flagrant d'éducation sexuelle appropriée en corée du sud. les 15 heures de cours obligatoires par an dans les lycées n'abordent pas des questions telles que l'égalité entre les sexes ou la contraception. et face à cet enseignement jugé trop traditionnaliste, certains parents inscrivent leurs enfants à des cours privés d'éducation sexuelle. mais le chemin est encore long dans un pays où même le mot " féministe " est encore considéré comme un gros mot.
─

──
► superbe l'éducation nationale dites donc.

text:
i never leave home without you!  in 1983 karl lagerfeld took the creative vision of chanel and i fell in love. i’m a chanel girl.  lagerfeld turned a sleeping beauty of a brand into gold and i love everything he’s touched. his influence transformed chanel and me!
lagerfeld had opinions on everything...
sweatpants (“a sign of defeat”) fur (“in a meat-eating world wearing leather for shoes and even clothes, the discussion of fur is childish”)
modeling and the #metoo movement (“if you don’t want your pants pulled about, don’t become a model!”) outspoken. opinionated. glorious. 
thank you for your 85 years.  you’ve made this girl smile a lot. xo

text:
yes, there is a time in my life that i am not proud of. there are names that make me cringe when i hear them. there are things i have experienced that many people will never know about. but, honestly who doesn't have a piece of their past they aren't proud of?
⚓
before cbd, if i bad any memory, of these experiences and names, it would drag me down into a panic attack. i would start shaking, feel my heart race, immediately draw back into defensive mode. i could cry right now, but only because i am realizing that i'm not scared of those memories anymore. i can have conversations about them and not feel like i need to rely on everyone else's strength, but now my own. ⚓
since cbd, i feel like i am free from the chain of my past. i have known that it is part of my story and why i am the person that i am, and know that that does not define who i am. now i am not afraid to process it or feel like i need to suppress those memories & experiences. ⚓
since cbd, i feel like i am in control of my own emotions again. for that, i couldn't be more blessed and thankful.
⚓
⚓

text:
“lorena,” amazon’s four-part true crime examination of the tabloid-driven media-feeding frenzy surrounding the crime and subsequent trial of lorena bobbitt, made its streaming platform debut over the weekend and nearly 26 years after the infamous deed. but "lorena," executive produced by jordan peele, proves substantially kinder to lorena than her ex in no small part due to the climate in which it comes into public view. "the circumstances surrounding the bobbitts' story contain within them the seeds of #metoo and female rage," writes melanie mcfarland. "lorena's presence on the witness stand during her trial, and the act that put her there, provide dramatic case studies in why women must be believed when they report rape and abuse." to read the full review, click the link in bio.
—
📷: ap

text:
let’s talk about intimacy after trauma. 
sexual abuse and assault have been hot topics recently in the media as women and men are becoming more empowered to come forward and talk about what has happened to them. this has caused a lot of victim shaming and animosity with a lot of people claiming the victims should have come forward sooner and that it is their responsibility. an easy claim to make when you’re not a victim.
someone on a comment thread told me that women shouldn’t get to play the ptsd card and that it’s their responsibility to inform police and their partners about abuse. to which i say, if that’s what you want, create the environment in which someone would feel comfortable sharing that information with you. also, ptsd is not a ‘card’ to be played. it’s a real affliction and does not only apply to war veterans. 
however, even in comfortable, trusting, committed relationships, it can still be difficult to address former abuse. ptsd rewires the brain and in some cases memories are blocked, while in others numerous triggers are created as the brain’s defense mechanism to signal when it feels in danger again. talking about events can lead to flashbacks, catatonic shock, and even violent outbursts. none of these responses are the victims’ fault and even with extensive therapy may not get totally better. evolutionary responses are not always subject to logic and reason. 
when it comes to being intimate with someone who has faced sexual trauma, it is best to be understanding, to not take it personally if they have a reaction, and not blame the person for an evolutionary response to abuse. create an environment of comfort, trust, and communication and it is entirely possible for the relationship to flourish. 
we don’t expect traumatized animals to ‘get over’ their past, we do everything we can to rehabilitate and help them. give the same deference to traumatized humans and be kind!
if you want to learn more about how trauma can change the brain, go to the link below!
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/pmc3181836/
•
•
#sexiestscience #intimacyandtrauma #ptsd #brainchanges #communicate #metoo #timesup

text:
i need to get something off my chest. i've been in the service industry for 10 years. during this time i have been grabbed and had my ass slapped more times than i can count. this past weekend about 10 different men grabbed my body and touched me. almost all of them stopped me in my tracks by grabbing my waist and/or shoulder and kept their hold while they told me whatever bullshit they wanted to say. grabbing another person is never okay. if you want to get someone's attention, use your words. if that's not working, a tap on the shoulder will do. you don't know what experiences and traumas people carry with them. grabbing someone's waist could be triggering and remind them of an assault. so, men (i say men because a woman has never inappropriately touched me), stop assuming that people want you to touch them. stop being offended when people tell you they don't want you to touch them. stop thinking that other people's bodies are objects for your pleasure or anything. just like your momma told you when you were little, keep your hands to yourself. it's really not a difficult concept. 
and to my fellow ladies, i know it's difficult and uncomfortable and you're generally in shock when someone decides that your body is for them but we have to call them out on this when it happens. we have to use our voices. we can not be silenced by anothers actions. we have to stick up for ourselves and for each other because no one else will. 
#stoptouchingme #mybodyismine #notyours #metoo

text:
amid another alleged sexual assault scandal, nelly was seen having a night out in miami over the weekend.

the “dilemma” rapper hit megaclub e11even with a group of guys and girls including dallas cowboys hall-of-famer michael irvin and longtime girlfriend shantel jackson in celebration of the club’s five-year anniversary on friday, an insider told page six.

dressed in a dolce & gabbana tracksuit, nelly performed a few of his hits including “e.i.” for the crowd before heading to his vip table.

the 44-year-old was seen “reminiscing” with irvin about co-starring in the movie “the longest yard,” and “partying together all night,” said the source. “nelly had a few drinks and shots casually,” the source added. “nothing wild, but he was having a great time.” he and his entourage danced and downed don julio 1942 until leaving the club just before 5 a.m.

last month, an anonymous woman sued nelly for sexual assault. nelly denies the allegations and is seeking dismissal of the suit.

this isn’t the artist’s first #metoo scandal.

in october 2017, accuser monique green claimed nelly raped her on his tour bus, but she dropped the charges and sued him for sexual assault and defamation that december. in september 2018, the parties agreed to drop the lawsuit and the case was dismissed.

irvin was also being investigated for allegedly sexually assaulting a woman in a florida hotel in march 2017, but prosecutors did not pursue charges after a rape kit test returned negative results.

other stars who turned up to celebrate e11even’s five-year anniversary this weekend include flo rida and a$ap rocky.

text:
*sitocanaunarespondemostodos*
*#yabasta*
*#vivasnosqueremos*

el machismo nos golpea a lo largo de toda nuestra vida, en el ámbito familiar y laboral, en nuestras relaciones sociales y de pareja, y una de sus expresiones más brutales es la violencia física y sexual. 
en méxico cada hora se violenta a 5 mujeres, 9 feminicidios se cometen al día, el 66,1 por cierto de las mujeres mayores de 15 años han sufrido algún tipo de agresión y según el inegi el nivel de delitos no denunciados es de 93,6 por ciento, las razones principales son: la impunidad, miedo a las consecuencias, miedo a ser culpadas por lo ocurrido, no saber cómo hacer la denuncia y no contar con ningún tipo de acompañamiento o asesoría. 
estas circunstancias son las que han orillado a millones de mujeres en todo el mundo a salir a dar la lucha sin cuartel contra el machismo, su justicia machista y su sistema. infinidad de mujeres hemos sacado la conclusión que nuestra lucha no sólo debe dirigirse hacia los individuos que nos agreden, sino contra el sistema que los ampara. esta terrible opresión es consentida y perpetuada por quienes ostentan el poder real —los grandes capitalistas—, y por toda la estructura institucional que los sostiene, desde las fiscalías, los tribunales y todo el aparato policial. 
en los últimos años hemos visto un despertar de la lucha feminista a nivel internacional, ha sido muy importante este avance, las manifestaciones multitudinarias contra el gobierno de trump, o el #metoo, así como el gran cordón humano en la india, demuestran la extensión y la fuerza de este gran movimiento por visibilizar la opresión de la mujer y poner un alto a toda la violencia que padecemos.

nuestro movimiento es legítimo porque luchamos por nuestro derecho a caminar seguras por las calles, por no ser intimidadas ni acosadas en nuestro entorno laboral, ni en nuestros hogares, por no ser asesinadas.

exigimos justicia y castigo ejemplar a los agresores de las miles de víctimas de feminicidio, de las miles de víctimas de violencia de cualquier tipo.

te llamamos a luchar y organizarte con nosotras y participar como contingente de ixtapaluca contra los feminicidios para la marcha del 8 de marzo

text:
if this aint the truth i don't know what else is. 
men expect women to dedicate our entire lives babying them, soothing them, massaging their ego and using our bodies to bear children who would not even answer our names. 
i can't remember who said it but someone once said: "men are taught to proritize themselves, women are taught to prioritize men". this leads to an unhealthy and very damaging imbalance
.

ladies, put yourself first and be unapologetically intentional about it. 
put your wellbeing first. 
put your emotional health first. 
prioritze your dreams and goals and refuse to be shamed for practising self love. 
aea fam, let's discuss. why do men love women sacrificing for them? comment below
.
.
.

text:
the time that child sexual abuse is 100% preventable is when a child tells the name of their abuser and that abuser is stopped.
✨
 otherwise, i think it is harmful and dangerous to say that child sexual abuse is 100% preventable. would we say that rape or assault is 100% preventable? that is a great goal but until we live in utopia it isn’t practical and i think it is a form of victim
blaming that denies that evil people exist that will always do the unimaginable to hurt someone.
✨
many times, prevention education puts an unreasonable responsibility to not be abused on the child and the adults in the child’s life instead of putting the responsibility for the abuse on the abuser. ✨
what does a child that has been abused think when they hear that what happened to them was 100% preventable? they think they did something wrong because obviously it happened to them. that is a horrible thing to do to an abused child that probably had guilt and shame used to abuse them. ✨
what does a parent think? they think they did something wrong and were responsible for their child being abused. what a horrible thing to do to a parent that was probably  betrayed in the most insidious way by someone they loved or trusted.
✨
of course we want to protect children. of course preventing abuse from happening is the goal, but we have to be careful with the messages being sent while doing it.  we must make sure that the message being given is that the responsibility for the abuse is the abuser’s alone. ✨
the only time child sexual abuse is 100% preventable is when a child says the name of their abuser and that abuser is stopped from ever harming again because that child was believed, protected, and defended 💞
✨
read sarah’s speech at the link in the bio ➡️ who will you choose to empower to see what happens to a child when they report abuse.
✨
i wrote a blog about the 3 things i want parents to know. you can read it at the link in the bio ➡️ one year later, what parents need to know
✨
highly recommend looking at @jessica_victimfocus resources on victim blaming. 
#justiceisprotectionandprevention #believeprotectdefend #traumainformedjusticesystem #believethechild #childsexualabuse

text:
just because your past [or present] may not be perfect, that does not disqualify you from the call that god has placed on your life.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
maybe you were left broken and overwhelmed. whether by the poor choices you made or the consequences of another’s actions, we can feel defeated by our situation, unable to see how everything wrong could be made right.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i was sexually abused from the ages 9-12... kicked out of college my freshman year... slept on my cousins couch in a 2 bedroom apartment with 3 other girls for a year and had my corporate coaching program rejected twice...
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but, look at me now! i used all that as fuel to create something bigger than me! 4 degrees and a successful coaching business later, now, i help other women take control of their lives and their earning potential.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i am a walking testimony that god isn’t ever going to allow your past to disqualify you from your dreams.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the painful experiences you have under your belt aren’t, in fact, the breaking of you, but very well could be the making of you. your painful experiences of the past don’t ever need to be swept under the rug and forgotten.

text: less than a day after it was announced that the man in the iconic 1945 #kissingsailor photo had died, a statue based on the photo in sarasota, florida was spray-painted with the words #metoo. for years, the "kissing sailor" symbolized the euphoria of victory in world war ii. but in recent years, the photo has been the subject of controversy. in 2005, the woman told a reporter that it "wasn't her choice" to be kissed, though she did say it was celebratory. police are searching for subjects, and say $1,000 in damage was down to the statue.

text:
proof that sexual harassment in the workplace doesn't always go unpunished... our client, a parole-probation officer for the michigan department of corrections, was recently rewarded a settlement of $1.1 million for the blatant, disgusting acts of sexual harassment committed against her. "i think the settlement speaks for itself," said jonathan marko, woods' detroit attorney. "i've never had a case where the michigan department of corrections voluntarily agreed to pay this much to right wrongs." https://www.freep.com/story/news/local/michigan/2019/01/22/parole-shannon-woods-sexual-harassment/2647709002/

text:
i always wore black, even in florida. ⁣⠀
⁣⠀
i look back on this picture and remember exactly how i felt in this moment. my shorts were too short, my top was too tight, and my 30+ pounds extra that i had just gained made me emotionally uncomfortable in every color besides black. i could've swore all the friends i hadn't seen in a year were all whispering behind my back. ⁣⠀
⁣⠀
it took 3 years for me to realize that the only one that could do anything about it was me. it was time to stop blaming my desk job for lack of movement. time to stop making the excuse that i was too tired after work. time to stop blaming the dryer for shrinking my clothes... again. i needed a wake up call that only i could give to myself. ⁣⠀
⁣⠀
i woke myself up. and with the help of nutrition plans that didn't leave me hungry (your girl here loves food, i wasn't about to give that up without a fight), a gym that traveled with me anywhere, and the accountability of a online community telling me that i could do anything i set my mind too, even when i couldn't see it myself. ⁣⠀

"eso es criminal! un puro desperdicio! este perfume podría haber sido vendido por más de un año de salario y entregado a los pobres ". se hincharon de ira, casi estallando de indignación por ella. pero jesús dijo: “déjala en paz. ¿por qué le estás haciendo pasar un mal rato? ella acaba de hacer algo maravillosamente significativo para mí ... ella hizo lo que pudo cuando pudo ... ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
what?! two of my pieces from my brand new #metoo series were just accepted into "persistence," a national juried show at d'art in norfolk, juried by lori pratico who is based in florida.

i researched her and was so impressed with her work that i decided to enter. so humbled to have been chosen by someone like her, a powerful artist and community activist. 
245 artist submitted 643 works from 39 states. pratico chose 46 works from 42 artists from 20 states. i was told that i was one of only two artists in the show who have two pieces juried in.  i am in a bit of grateful disbelief.

i'm not going to show my pieces here because i hope you will come to the opening from 5:30 to 7:30 on march 14 in norfolk. (this image is the show logo; not sure of the artist.) #contemporaryartist #contemporaryart #practicingartist #teachingartist
name: Betsy DiJulio

text:
the women’s center is looking for volunteers to help out with the 2019 sisterhood dinner on february 25th! shifts vary between 2:00pm and 8:45pm. interested in signing up to help out? visit go.ncsu.edu/sisterhoodvolunteer. 
the sisterhood dinner celebrates the contributions and accomplishments of nc state women. it was originally called the susan b. anthony dinner but was changed in 1999 to the sisterhood dinner to encompass all aspects of the achievements of women.

the speaker for the night will be jessica holmes, the chair of the wake county board of commissions. 
the theme for the 2019 sisterhood dinner is “leading change; inspiring action”. from movements such as #blacklivesmatter and #metoo, to the midterm elections producing one of the most diverse classes of incoming elected officials in recent history, the momentum towards leading efforts for social change is both visible and inspiring. help us to center and uplift the movements, work and leadership of women. this year’s sisterhood dinner theme is intended to not only showcase those in our community who are doing the work to create social change, but to challenge all participants to be instigators of change. we all have a role to play in creating a more equitable and just campus and community.

text_retweet:
repost from @simplexactivism || having moved from an ultra conservative town in tx to nyc, i feel like so many people here have no idea how queer people in other parts of the country live. same-sex intercourse is still in the books as being illegal in my state, and you even hear about people getting arrested for it every once in a while (though thankfully judges now have to throw it out). my middle and high schools had rules against being queer or trans, and would expel students if they came out. internalized homophobia and transphobia led me to contemplate suicide from a young age. while this is common in christian communities across the country, it’s almost unheard of here. many people here were shocked when an art teacher near where i lived in texas was fired for telling students she had a wife when asked, having no idea that this is not only legal, but common. it’s also important to recognize that some states that protect lgb people from work and housing discrimination don’t protect tgnc individuals. i hope one day places like my hometown will have the same legal protections for queer and trans individuals that we enjoy here in nyc. much love to organizations like @splcenter that are working to make this dream a reality 💕 
#lgbt #lesbian #gay #bisexual #trans #transgender #nonbinary #queer #queerliberation #civilrights #lgbtrights #civilliberties #discrimination #employmentdiscrimination #bigotry #nohateinmystate #texas #nyc #feminist #queersurvivors #metoo #homophobia #transphobia #systemicoppression

.
.

text:
gender pay gap reporting, getting it right...
last april saw the introduction of mandatory gender pay gap reporting for businesses.

are you ready for this year’s deadline of 5th april 2019?

employers with 250 employees or more must calculate and publish
the mean (average) and median (mid-point) gender pay gap

the mean and median bonus gender pay gap

the proportion of men and the proportion of women in the organisation receiving a bonus payment

the proportion of men and women in each quartile pay band. (see link in bio for more info).

text: i grew up on the beaches of sarasota as a child. i also grew up admiring this statue and when i was old enough my dad told me the real story behind it.this statue meant a lot to me, as a child and as an adult. i cannot believe the level of disrespect that someone would have to vandalize something like this. i don’t care what your political beliefs are, or where you stand on the #metoo movement, but for someone to be so disrespectful to not only those depicted in the statue and the state of florida, is appalling. i am so disappointed in whoever is responsible. my feelings are truly truly hurt. #sarasota #unconditionalsurrender #heartbroken

text: as some of you might know, as well as being an artist, i’m also a visual analyst. i am, unfortunately, well aware of how history is altered as my two years of groundbreaking research as head of visual research and photo archives at the dedalus foundation, nyc, the estate of robert motherwell, published in the catalgue raisonee was attributed to a male colleague. //// as a visual analyst, i observe things as much as i see them. in this statue on the right, it is important not only to “see”, but “observe” how the artist has chosen to alter the poses from the original photograph. we learn from this how history gets changed in the retelling under the pretense of being “art”: it gets sanitized, romanticized, whitewashed. //// on the right is a statue modeled after the in/famous post wwii kissing sailor photograph, titled “unconditional surrender”. starting with the title, the creator of the statue has also taken liberties with the forms of the figures, and - as i learned early on from leonard baskin in “the shape of content” how shape and content are intertwined - what is most significant here is how the shapes, angles and postures are changed, softened in order to convey a sense and feeling of ease and willing “surrender”, which was not, as we know, the case in the original photograph. note, in the original, her clenched fist, twisted legs, contorted back and obscured - indeed, obliterated - face. //// in art, as in life, it is important not only to “see”, but “observe”. it is critical to not just “ask”, but question: to not just “decide”, but discern. #metoo #kissingsailor #art #history #arthistory #photography #sanitized #romanticized #whitewash #observation #visualthinking #visualthinkingstrategies #robertmotherwell #abstractexpressionism #research #questioneverything #askquestions #discernment #discern #criticalthinking #creativeprocess #creativethinking #thebutterflyprocess #visitingartists #leonardbaskin

🖤
edit: thank you to everyone who has sent me a lovely message. please don’t worry about me, though!
📷: @ms_veness

text:
yes this post is blunt.  it needs to be said though. our hormones affect the way we feel and it’s wise to watch our own behavioral patterns. developing tools that help you cope with the facts of life (periods, pregnancy, etc) help keep your sanity.  i can’t believe the amount of male psychiatrists i had that wanted to “stabilize my mood,”with psychiatry. i became more crazy, more confused...like no thanks i’ll get my mood stabilizers from my food, sleep, & healthy lifestyle patterns...when i don’t sleep or eat right, that makes me moody and off..that doesn’t make me special..it’s common sense.  men need those things, too! anger, sadness, happiness, these are emotions..and we have them because we are human.  stand together and don’t put up with psychiatric abuse.

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
quietly reminding myself of this as i step into exciting but fearful things with my nonprofit. anyone else like me 🙋🏻‍♀️ and feel super unqualified and insecure about their ability to step into their call? 
running a non-profit is not easy. i’ve literally sat on panels in front of hundreds of people while the other speakers told the audience i wasn’t qualified just because i don’t have a social work degree. i’ve been told i’m intimidating, too passionate, too loud and that i don’t have the business acumen to be successful. i’ve watched as other nonprofits have implemented my ideas and called them their own and have had groups of organizations physically remove resources for survivors because it had my name on it and not theirs. some where along the way, those lies seeped into my ability to believe in myself and made me forget the fact that the experience i carry of working with 82 survivors of trafficking and doing outreach to over 1,000 women working in the sex industry uniquely qualifies me to do my job and step into the scary things. and no one can take that away from me. 
whatever you’ve experienced, both good and bad, has uniquely prepared you for the next season! those next scary steps are yours to own and your prepared in more ways than you know. no one can take away your experience. it’s yours and yours alone and uniquely qualifies you to step into the scary! 
#bohostyle #boholife #bossbabe #boss #socialjusticewarrior #pursuepretty #entrepreneur #nonprofitlife #endtrafficking #metoo #metoomovement

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
¿has oído hablar del pussyhat project? @p_ssyhatproject

este proyecto nació en el 2017 para participar en la marcha por las mujeres (women's march) en estados unidos.

también es considerado un movimiento social enfocado en los derechos humanos y en la concienciación de los problemas que afectan a las mujeres como el acoso, el racismo, etc.

este año en tejedores de costa rica queremos involucrarnos en este proyecto y por tanto te invitamos a tejer tu gorrito rosado (también conocido como #pussyhat) para usarlo el 8 de marzo, el día de la mujer. día que conmemora los hechos sucedidos el 8 de mazo de 1857 en new york, donde obreras textiles protestaron por los pésimas condiciones en las que trabajaban.

reposted from @earthlove777 -  rp @lightmoveme 🔥plastic waste is one of many types of wastes that take too long to decompose. normally, plastic items can take up to 1000 years to decompose in landfills. but plastic bags we use in our everyday life take 10-1000 years to decompose, while plastic bottles can take 450 years or more.
▪️since the 1950s, around 8.3 billion tons of plastic have been produced worldwide. that’s equivalent to the weight of more than 800,000 eiffel towers.
▪️and only 9% of it has been recycled.
▪️a report by the guardian found that 1 million plastic bottles are bought around the world every minute, and this number is set to increase by another 20% by 2021 if we don’t act.
▪️the same report said more than 480 billion plastic drinking bottles were purchased in 2016 across the world up from 300 billion a decade ago.
▪️additionally, less than half of the bottles purchased in 2016 were recycled — with just 7% of those collected turned into new bottles, and the rest ending up in landfill sites or the ocean.
▪️worldwide, about 2 million plastic bags are used every minute.
▪️this might seem like an unbelievable number, but according to ecowatch, between 500 billion and 1 trillion plastic bags are used worldwide annually.
▪️ the average time that a plastic bag is used for is 12 minutes. yep, that’s right they’re used for an average of 12 minutes and then take up to 1 thousand years to decompose. #respectlife #respect #planetearth #earth #oceanavenue #animallovers #animalkingdom #familyiseverything #savetheocean #savetheearth #peaceandlove #govegan #crueltyfree #environment #environmentalist #planetearth #metoo #plastic #politicón #animalshaverights #pollution #babyanimals #donttakeourplanetforgranted - #regrann

text:
“i was 24 years old when i came to nyc to become an actress. i took a job as a waitress in a diner in queens. there i encountered so much harassment from males that i can’t remember all of it. from nasty customers telling me all kind of things, getting offers to be in threesomes with their wives, the cooks asking me very personal things like “do you shave down there? do you have it like a baby?”, getting compliments or nasty comments everytime i would go to the kitchen. 
but, this is where it gets worse. my boss, the manager, often would pass by in the very tight kitchen and touch my boobs and my ass. i was so nervous every time he did that. i didn’t know what to do. i would laugh nervously and pretend it didn’t happen. he would do it anytime his girlfriend, who was also working there, wasn’t around. this lasted about a year, until i spoke to the owner and said that i will sue him for harrasment. the owner fired him and told me not to sue anybody. so i left that job. i cried so much everyday, feeling impotent and guilty with fear that he would do something to me one day. also, i found out that i wasn’t the only one going through that. my coworkers, who were immigrants, were afraid to talk because they didn’t have papers and were afraid of being deported.” - @malena.ramirez

text:
january 2011. brief encounter with him, when i was still a law student dreaming about fashion and falling in love with paris. he was about to get in his hummer but he stopped and turned around when he heard our shy call in poor french with a heavy brazilian accent. after this day i was sure i would come back one day and work in the fashion capital of the world. he was the last of the great ones. this is the end of an era.

ele não foi um santo, muito pelo contrário. já deu várias declarações racistas, machistas, falou mal de imigrantes e do #metoo. mas definitivamente foi um gênio. não existe chanel sem coco chanel e sem karl lagerfeld. a história da moda seria completamente outra sem ele. cai o último dos gigantes e abre-se um novo capítulo.

text: #abuseofpower • “the clergy role carries a great deal of power in and of itself, and one of the most insidious aspects of that power is the role of "man of god." in some sense the minister carries ultimate spiritual authority, particularly in the eyes of a trusting parishioner who looks to him for spiritual guidance and support. but the male minister also possesses other forms of power: as a man, he carries the power society confers upon men and socializes them to hold over women, often in the guise of being their protectors. he is often physically stronger and more imposing. he may be an employer. he may also assume a teaching or mentoring role which encourages women to listen to his advice and correction. often he also functions as a counselor, with all the transference inherent in such a relationship.” — rev. pamela cooper white

text: "when adults like donna grow up with parents that look to their children for saving, it would make sense that as a child the survival rationale would be "i need to take care of my sisters/mom/family members in order to be worthy of love and connection." this is how the adaptation of responsibility becomes problematic in adult life, in particular in professional settings. unconsciously we can put a heavy burden on ourselves to be the savior to someone else. even without early childhood experiences this would lead to burnout in jobs where that burden would just become unreasonable and unbearable. but when trauma is a part of that adaptive picture, it can activate all of the unconscious "fear of death" (survival) body memories along with the associated biochemicals and hormones and create out blown feelings of panic and anxiety when we become fearful that our clients, patients, students, friends or family members continue to struggle or suffer. many times this becomes an actual detriment to the forward movement accessible to others, because as we feel responsible for saving them, they become dependent on us. they remain dis-empowered. to work through this adaptation we need to be aware of what we are feeling in our bodies when we start to panic about the health and happiness of others, and use our own empowered resources to rewire our adaptations. the good news is that we can actually help empower those we care about by sharing these things with them."#writersofinstagram #selflove #selfhelp #recovery #authorsofinstagram #trauma #traumarecovery #yoga #mindfulness #men  #metoo  #community #women #woman #womenempowerment #children #kid

text:
#isc2018semifinalist 
i just received an email from the isc that announced that my song "designer girl" has been awarded a semi-finalist position with finalists to be revealed in the coming weeks.  this is now another record of mine that can potentially hold another finalist spot as did "insecurity (#metoo)" in the uk.  semi-finalist positions are great achievements in this competition due to there being over 19,000 submissions as in contrast to the uk songwriting competition which drew about 5,500.  furthermore, the isc awards cash prizes!  overall, i'm honored that a new genre i'm creating from my tribal and african roots has made an impact on the global songwriting stage with the message of #femaleempowerment . "no high fashion design could have created your unique design, and you don't need the designer clothes to be beautiful; your design is beautiful enough"... thank you #internationalsongwritingcompetition !!! #greatthingsfor2019 #moretocome #junkanoo #junkanew #birthofanewgenre #newsounds #songwriter #recordproducer #newbeginnings #blackhistorymonth #blackexellence #african #caribbean #bahamas #designergirl #paragonicentertainment #klevarsmith

i just received an email from the isc that announced that my song "designer girl" has been awarded a semi-finalist position with finalists to be revealed in the coming weeks.  this is now another record of mine that can potentially hold another finalist spot as did "insecurity (#metoo)" in the uk.  semi-finalist positions are great achievements in this competition due to there being over 19,000 submissions as in contrast to the uk songwriting competition which drew about 5,500.  furthermore, the isc awards cash prizes!  overall, i am honored that a new genre i am creating from my tribal and african roots has made an impact on the global songwriting stage with the message of #femaleempowerment . text:
*trigger warning: survivor recollections* .
stolen innocence
.
“my memory was triggered like a tripwire one afternoon on a middle-school playground while my girlfriends gave giggled descriptions of what older girls do on dates. listening to them with a blank gaze i realized i wasn’t exactly a stranger to those acts. the flood gates had opened. most of the details are still blurred as my subconscious clings to this protective blockage but some of it has slipped through. i have one very vivid memory standing in the shower as blood streamed down my legs from what i can only assume was a broken hymen - i was seven years old.” #survivorstories #childhoodsexualabuse #triggerwarning #repression #copingskills #sexualassaulteducation #sexualassault #metoo #timesup #believesurvivors #stoleninnocence

text:
во вторник полицейские в г. сарасота, штат флорида, обнаружили, что на статуе, созданной на основе известной фотографии “поцелуй на таймс-сквер”, появилась надпись #metoo. это произошло через два дня после того, как скончался один из героев снимка – ветеран второй мировой войны джордж мендонса. 
надпись была удалена. 
хэштег #metoo стал символом кампании против сексуального насилия. в октябре 2017 он стал активно распространяться в соцсетях, сопровождая истории жертв домогательств. (фото: sarasota police department)

text:
a day after the sailor seen kissing a woman in the iconic world war ii photo died, a statue commemorating the couple was found vandalized early tuesday, florida police said.
🔸
according to the sarasota pd, the vandal used red spray paint to emblazon the phrase "#metoo," which refers to the movement against sexual assault and harassment. .
authorities were dispatched to the unconditional surrender statue in downtown sarasota after midnight tuesday and discovered red lettering covering the length of the nurse's leg. after a canvas of the area, officers did not find other objects that were defaced. sarasota pd said there's no available surveillance video that captured the incident and no known witnesses. they believe it happened between the mid-afternoon and evening hours, but, it is unknown exactly what time.
.
."the approximate damage is estimated to be more than $1,000 due to the large area that the graffiti covers, and the resources needed to repair it," police said. 
george mendonsa, the ecstatic sailor shown kissing a woman in times square celebrating the end of wwii, died monday at the age of 95 – two days before his 96th birthday. he was shown kissing greta zimmer friedman, a dental assistant in a nurse's uniform, on aug 14, 1945. known as v-j day, it was the day japan surrendered to the united states.
.
the photo by alfred eisenstaedt became one of the most famous photographs of the 20th century. it was years before mendonsa and friedman were confirmed to be the couple. friedman died in 2016 at age 92. "it was the moment that you come back from the pacific, and finally the war ends," mendonsa told cbs news' michelle miller in 2012.
.
during the #metoo era the timeless kiss has been seen in a less positive light. critics argue the photograph didn't depict romance because mendonsa, who said he was drinking, simply grabbed and kissed friedman without knowing her. "i did not see him approaching, and before i know it i was in this vice grip," friedman told cbs news.
.
others said the image was symbolic of a time when men controlled women and normalized sexual assault. "it was just somebody really celebrating," friedman said in a 2005 interview. #wwii
