so needless to say, i’m pretty excited that girladrift is going to share a little bit about their healing journey (ps: if you couldn’t tell, they’re super into derby, so i bet that you’ll hear about how derby has influenced their healing journey!). i don’t want to give too much away, so i’ll stop there! please join me in welcome girladrift as our february takeover!

text: this week my students are approaching the powerful new article laurie halse anderson wrote about her memoir speak 20 years after its publication and the conversations she continues to have with students about what consent looks like in the 21st century. the article is powerful and uncomfortable and in many ways so heartbreaking thah it was written now in 2019, post #metoo and it’s still so damn relevant. it’s a hard article to read. she writes about hearing young men say to her, “i may have pushed it too far,” and “i didn’t hear her say no,” and how she has had to swallow her rage and hear them as they try to reconcile their actions. it’s a hard article. pushing our students out of their comfort zones is critical to allowing them to grow. we need to trust our students more to see themselves in the curriculum and to question it and consider issues that really connect to what they go through on a daily basis walking our hallways and in their social media feeds. i’ll share their poignant ideas later this week but for now i’m giving them the space to deal with this disquieting article in their notebooks first. notebooks that i might never read or will only read if they request it. notebooks can be a safe place to confront very scary ideas.

text_retweet:
tahu hak anda dan bayi anda semasa kelahiran!

ramai ibu yang risau akan layanan semasa melahirkan berbanding dengan kelahiran itu sendiri!

adakah anda bersedia?

#betterbirthdecision #betterbirthmalaysia

#repost @birthmonopoly (@get_repost)
・・・
🎉🎉 know your rights is here!! 🎉🎉 (link in profile)
.

a midwife seemed like a good fit for me until she told me i needed to schedule an induction once i went past 41 weeks.  i never got a good reason why.
.
so, at 41 weeks and 6 days pregnant, with the help of my doula, i switched to a different hospital and midwife, who was willing to lay out all my options and support me in my *free* choice about what i wanted to do.  i was really lucky to find a care provider who was willing to take me that late in pregnancy.  i ended up having my baby the very next day with no complications in a respectful environment with no unnecessary medical intervention.
.
but i didn’t really know my rights.  i didn’t really think i *needed* to know my rights--until i got in hot water.
.
everything worked out just fine, but the whole thing left me with a lot of questions about my own rights in that situation. what might have happened if another care provider hadn’t turned up for me?  what rights did i have to stand on, what rights belonged to me, to protect myself and my baby? .
the more i researched and spoke with other people who had given birth, the more surprised i was to realize what strong rights i had had to say no, and how commonly that right is violated in maternity care.
.
that was seven years ago!  today, i'm releasing know your rights: legal and human rights in childbirth for birth professionals & advocates (link in profile)--a product of years working with top lawyers and advocates trying to untangle this dilemma.  it's a must for anyone working in birth.  period.
.

the rage this sparked has not quietly simmered away.
it is still raw and burning. that feeling will never escape thousands of sisters.

thoughts?

text:
these are just two examples, but they are very common ones. mind games and gaslighting are two main components to narcissistic abuse. they will make the victim believe that the victim is the problem, and in turn, the victim will begin to actually shut down and lose self confidence. one of the reasons why victims lose this self-esteem is because they believe they’re the problem. they are full of guilt and shame—two things a narcissist will never feel or admit to. so you tell me: how can you be the narcissist if you are capable of such feelings?

text:
“do justice, love mercy, live humbly." former @judgerenee campaign slogan provides a window into her benevolent and amazingly kind heart. her compassion is a force to be reckoned with, as we've witnessed in her years as a judge for the 150th and 73rd districts of san antonio. 
inspired by a startlingly large gap in the system towards foster teens, yanta created pearls court to assist teenage girls in foster care to overcome adversity. #pearlscourt stands for preparation, esteem, achievement, resiliency, learning, strength, and stamina - all important tools for girls to come through the foster system as confident, capable and empowered women. when an oyster goes through hardship, it produces a pearl. yanta's vision for #pearlscourt  is to provide a safe space for girls to learn how to turn their pain into power. 
in honor of yanta’s 59th birthday, you can donate to this incredible cause by visiting the link in our bio 🌺✨ #womeninbusiness #girlpower #ceo #womenempowerment #womenentrepreneurs #womensupportingwomen #womeninbiz #feminism #feminist #metoo #timesup #womenempoweringwomen #girlbosssa #savvybusinessowner #risingtidesociety #communityovercompetition #bandofgirlgang #dontquityourdaydream #flashesofdelight #entrepreneurlifestyle #theeverydayproject #creativepreneur #womeninlaw #womeninthelegalsystem #womenlawyers #womenjudge #judgeship

text: join us thursday, feb 21, 2019 at 7:15 pm for our monthly healing circle + whirling (sufi dance) + prayer led by crs co-founders yasuko kasaki and christopher pelham and sufi dance artist lale sayoko. we gather to let go of our small selves and remember our divinity within. musician lulla layla will be with us to play the tanbour and sing during our whirling. bring in any issue — relationship trauma, #metoo, disease, money issue, depression — and surrender it to spirit. remember who you are. receive new guidance. experience love's presence. heal yourself and others. https://crsny.org/index.php/event/crs-healing-circle-meditation-whirling-prayer/

text:
good fucking riddance, dude. 
this guy was such an asshole. here’s an excerpt of an article about him:
lagerfeld had a habit of complaining about women’s bodies, whether he was saying they looked ugly or need to lose weight. he called adele “a little too fat,” as an aside while discussing her lovely voice, and later insulted plus-sized women again: “no one wants to see curvy women on the catwalk.” he also grumbled about other people's faces. in 2012, he insulted pippa middleton saying the duchess of cambridge is beautiful, but “her sister struggles. i don’t like the sister’s face. she should only show her back.” worst of all, lagerfeld dismissed objections to sexual harassment in the industry. he told numero magazine last spring that he was "fed up" with the #metoo movement. "if you don’t want your pants pulled about," he said, "don’t become a model! join a nunnery, there’ll always be a place for you in the convent."
g o o d b y e 👏

text:
don’t be dumb...
.
.
daughter just came home today and told me one of her closest friends came out to her and told her they were gay.  being the dope kid that she is she was completely supportive.  i told her i was so proud of her and told her did she know how important it was for her to give her friend a safe space to open up and come out.  i told her that for many...that was the hardest part - to come out to friends and family and be met with a supportive, loving response.  i said, for many in the lgbt community that was never a positive experience.  she just looked at me all dumbfounded and confused and was like, “why?  we’re all different.  people are dumb.  we should love people no matter what or who they like.” 💯🙌🏾👏🏾💜
.
.
uhhh...i could’ve died in that moment the proudest father that ever lived 😍💕 💗#dontbedumb #ally #loveislove

text:
remember to text your friends today. you never know who needs a simple hello. i'm going to be honest, i love my life but it's not all rainbows and sunshine... you know theres no rainbows without some rain! the past few days have been a little rough on me and anxiety has been creeping up on me but today i had a little counseling session and boy oh boy did i need that maintenance and reminder. she didn't tell me anything that i don't already tell myself, it's just that release and venting that helps clear my mind and helps me feel better. i don't tell you this for sympathy, i tell you so that you can see everyone has bad days, no matter how good their life looks. i am a survivor of childhood sexual abuse, ptsd, and myasthenia gravis! i have fought too hard to be where i am in my life to just give in and give up. it's ok if you fall 1,000 times...just make sure you get up 1,001 times!! live your life and love it! the good and the bad! whatever you're going through is temporary so just learn through the journey and enjoy it, because it is making you!! 💪❄💋 . .
.
.
.
#mgcantstopme #mentalhealthawareness #yourstoryisntoveryet #breakthesilence #ptsd #invisibleillness #anxiety #spoonie #spoonielife #spreadlove #chingona #momlife #latina #selfcare #selflove #positivevibes #inspiration #blessingindisguise #metoo #onlythestrongsurvive #youmatter #venividivici #changingtheworld #spooniemermaid #weallgrow #bossbabe #aspiretoinspire #textyourfriendtuesday

text:
agar kita terhindar dari modus mulut manis penyair! "jika rasa menjadi pembenaran untuk memerkosa, di mana logika manusiamu? perkosaan itu bukan soal rasa tapi soal relasi kuasa. dengarkan jerit suara korban. mereka terluka dan butuh disembuhkan. adil kah jika pelaku dibiarkan berkeliaran? saat trauma korban bisa saja berkepanjangan. jika memang kita di sini bicara soal rasa dan manusia, kenapa tak ikut desak dpr sahkan ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual?  bela korban dan jangan biarkan pelaku bebas berkelana. sahkan ruu p-ks!" kenapa harus peduli dengan kekerasan seksual yang dialami orang lain? kekerasan seksual dapat terjadi pada siapapun termasuk dirimu. maka mulailah peduli terhadap kekerasan seksual yang dialami orang lain. membangun keberanian untuk melawan bisa dimulai dengan peduli terhadap orang lain. untuk membangun lingkungan yang bebas kekerasan seksual butuh kekeuatan dan keberanian banyak orang, maka kepedulian menjadi hal mutlak.
____________

text:
most brands wouldn't be too pleased if their super bowl commercial was the lowest-scoring ad in the @usatoday ad meter (and the weakest performer on every metric @ace_metrix tracks). not @burgerking, which infamously served up 45 seconds of andy warhol eating a whopper for super bowl liii. 
cmo fernando machado said that the low ranking is actually … a good thing: "we're very proud of that." "we have never seen such a strong shift in brand attributes like what we've seen with this campaign." read more from @fermachado123 in our cover story by @jwohl -- link in bio. 🍔
also in our latest issue: five campaigns that helped shatter african-american stereotypes (including @nike and @wiedenkennedy's 1980s ads starring @officialspikelee and #michaeljordan), a q&aa with #metoo founder @taranajaneen and new twists in "corngate" keep the beer kings foaming. 🍺
🎨: annick poirier, @tamagotcheese

text:
i’m so honored and delighted to speak at penn state university with #metoo movement founder tarana burke on a topic that means so much to me. it's a history making moment and i'm forever proud to have found my voice and can use my speaking platform to build my 50 shades of silence movement in order to help so many people.

i'm also so excited about being a visibility coach and helping people design their signature topic so they can speak and influence.

what subject or topic means so much to you?

do you know how many speaking opportunities you are missing out on?

do you even know how to find speaking engagements and opportunities?

you deserve to be speaking on the stages about the causes that mean the most to you too.

that's why i created all rise, an exclusive coaching experience and retreat for woman who are ready to get their signature topic and talk done! 
www.darieth.com/allrise

it's coming up on may 16th- 19th and oct 17th -20th in  miromar lakes, fl. this is a beautiful setting for you to develop your signature topic and talk and create an expansive vision for the impact your are ready to make in the world.

you will see where you can schedule a call with at www.darieth.com/allrise to learn more.

let's get you ready, so the next time you hear about a conference on the topic that matters most to you, you will be the one they are featuring on stage.

you can do this and i'm here to show you how, schedule a call with me to find out.

text:
can share my story?
the photos were taken by me. [part 1]
i was always an independent girl, i didn’t like michele the girly stuff.
since my young age i prefer to be among adults.
i traveled by myself, i lived in different countries by myself, i listened a lot and define my opinions. 
i always respected myself.

after a couple of years outside my home country i returned. i was not sure about my future, at the same time i was turning 30, i taught it should be time to slow down and organize my life.
i got involved with a long time no-see friend. 
it was nice.. but not with the respect i was used to. i accepted and taught it may change.

when i was a teenager, i believed i could help some disoriented young boy to organized his life.
when this old friend appeared on my life, i taught it my be my turn.. still not sure if it was.. .
. photo: lima, peru, 2009
#beginnings #newbeginnings #womenempowerment #womensupportwomen #strongerwoman #strongertogether #metoo #dreams #teenagerdream #girldreams #mystory

text:
#derechoaltiempo hoy se giró una orden de captura internacional contra el sacerdote mauricio víquez lizano, quien se dio a la fuga tras ser acusado por el delito de violación en perjuicio de un menor de edad.
esta no es la única denuncia contra víquez a quien hace 16 años víctimas de abusos sexuales denunciaron ante altos jerarcas de la iglesia católica quienes no hicieron más que cambiarlo de parroquia.
después de esto víquez fue incluso nombrado vocero en temas de familia y no fue hasta mayo del año pasado que le suspendieron del sacerdocio. 
tras leer los horribles testimonios de las víctimas decidí hacer estas fotos.

#metoo #yotecreo #lightgraffiti #photography #canon

text:
vanessa tyson speaks about the #metoo movement in first public appearance since accusing justin fairfax of sexual assault
#
in her first public appearance since accusing virginia lt. gov justin fairfax of sexual assault, vanessa tyson spoke to an audience at stanford university about sexual consent, the #metoo movement and recurring attempts in society to undermine the credibility of victims of sexual assault. “this is credibility that i think we need to get away from and move away from because every woman matters, every survivor matters, regardless of her background,” tyson said. “none of us are disposable or dispensable.” tyson appeared as a panelist at a symposium titled “betrayal and courage in the age of #metoo” and hosted by stanford’s center for advanced study in the behavioral sciences, where tyson is currently a fellow researching the political discourse surrounding sexual violence. the sold-out event, where reporters gathered in an overflow room, was planned several months before tyson publicly came forward last week, accusing fairfax of forcing her to perform oral sex during an encounter in july 2004 at the democratic national convention in boston. fairfax has vehemently denied the allegation. tyson appeared calm and in command as she discussed issues surrounding sexual assault, but she did not address her own, widely publicized account of sexual assault. tyson, a 42-year-old…

text:
for those of you here just for the art, continue at your discretion as the following deals with sexual abuse.
.
you can read this woman’s full story on @lovewhatmatters from the link in her profile @brittianknowsbest.
.
“for years i have let you haunt my brain. the questions of why never stop flowing through my head. why can’t you tell the truth for once? a man is not a coward, he owns up to his mistakes even if it destroys himself. you decided to adopt me. you decided to take my father away. and it sickens me because it was only for your guilty pleasure. you never loved me. you only saw me as a tool or a weapon. i was your property. i refuse to be your property anymore. i want to stand up for what is right even if it destroys me. i will not be a coward and hide in the shadows. i want people to know who you truly are instead of the perfect man you claim to be. i didn’t bring you to court to destroy my life, i brought you to court to prove to myself that i can be strong enough to overcome you. i look at you today and all i see is a sick pathetic man that loves children. a man that loves to control, manipulate, and destroy. i see a man who deserves nothing, but has everything. i see a man who emotionally and physically ruined my body. i see a man who gets to walk out today a free man because he waited until i was of age to leave a paper trail in hopes that he would get love in return. it’s pathetic really. you get to walk out of this court room today and live on with your life in denial while i deal with the pain you put upon me. i never asked for any of this. i never asked for a creepy man to become obsessed with me, but yet you’re the one that everyone seems to protect. somehow you become the victim while i was the one that everyone questioned even with proof. i lost my mother. i lost my brother. i lost my entire family because of you. i was alone and scared while you had the comfort of many. no matter what happens today though, i win. i win because i faced you. i stood up for myself when all of you thought i would run and hide. i am showing everyone who tim really is. a cowardly man who loves children.”
name: Amanda Newman Art

text:
karl lagerfeld’s passing was quite unexpected for me. i am saddened that such a huge influencer in the fashion world is gone, but i also can’t help but think of all the things he’s said over the years.

i have never been able to afford his clothes, nor have i ever been able to fit into his clothes, and he has made it abundantly clear that was the way he wanted it. but still i have to look to designers like him in order to find inspiration and trends for my job in the fashion industry as a textile designer. chanel is such an iconic brand and he had done some great things with it, but him as a person made it harder and harder for me to personally support him. unfortunately, i’m not in a position in my company or in the industry to oppose his influence and have to silently take his lead. for my own work, i look to designers like christian siriano who try to make fashion accessible to so many different types of women, both in range of sizing and different price points. i hope the fashion industry can continue forward and make it a better place for not only the customers, but also the models, workers, and find better sources for materials.

reform is on the way.
.
#karl #karllagerfeld #fashion #rip #ripkarllagerfeld #chanel #cocochanel #metoo #cosplay #closetcosplay #bodypositive 
@csiriano

text:
in 1998 i organized a seminar for my sorority on the objectification on women's bodies and had my women's studies professor speak at it. i can't remember her name but i remember that night. thought about it heavily while i prepared my presentation on the stigma of breastfeeding in public in atlanta. 20 years later. sometimes i wonder if this type of thinking will ever go away. 
the one thing that has shifted is the narrative and the power behind it. women's bodies are beautiful and sexy. doesn't mean the ads to sell burgers using boobs should be given more respect than a mom breastfeeding. 
#womensbodies #womensrights #women #metoo #speaker #feminism #atlanta #breastfeeding #momlife #sexy #smart #powerful #astropriya #priyanembhard

text:
my daddy heard my prayers ❣️(sharing) 
i talk to my daddy all the time. although he is no longer here in the physical, he is with me now more than ever! i asked  my daddy to send me someone that he knows. i wanted to be of service. my father sent me his younger brother who looks just like him! he lives two hours away from atlanta. we have been bonding and i am so happy! this is my uncle roland. doesn't he look like my daddy! well, i drove up to him today to spend time with him and took him to his doctors appointment and did some things around his house for him. my sun rodney flagg went with me and set some things up for my uncle. he has health issues but he gets up and shows up everyday regardless, with the biggest smile and a heart of gratitude in spite of. this  brings me so much joy! he is such a joy and reminds me of my daddy so much! they are so much alike! i plan to take good care of my uncle and make sure he's good! my heart is so full of joy right now! won't he do it!! just wanted to share! love you and thanks for reading! be love! be light! the world has enough hatred. l's up! always. love is a movement‼️❤️ #lovemovement  #lovetrumpshate365 #author #playwright #host #brandambassador #healer #actress #activist #motivationalspeaker #domesticviolence #rape #abuse #metoo  #evolving #theloudestsilence #mirrorstruereflections #feliciteelove

text:
my birthday was last month. yep, i’m 36!! for my 36th year, i want to get my picture taken by a professional to document the year i kicked some major ass. -
this morning, i had the opportunity to speak to a group of women who have shared experiences in both physical and emotional abuse. the time spent with these amazing women was raw and powerful. being able to have the platform to speak my truth is and will continue to be my way of fighting back and standing up for myself. he no longer has that hold over me. he no longer has the ability to diminish my light. i know that i am loved and have a community of women who support me in prayer and encouragement and lots of hugs. for i plan to shine ever so brightly and love ever so immensely!! -
i just want to let all women who have suffered and are suffering physical and emotional abuse or any trauma i see you. i hear you. i care. you are loved.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
#pinklovers 💗 he notado un comportamiento común entre los humanos 🤷🏼‍♀️que cuando alguien muere, los comentarios son positivos, nadie habla mal del que murió, menos de sus defectos,eras un genio, el mejor en tu profesión, linda gente, ícono. en el caso de las celebridades empiezan aparecer fotos del baúl de los recuerdos etc 💗 esto de la muerte es complejo, yo siendo una simple mortal desearía que todos los que me conocen o estén en contacto conmigo me digan todo lo que sienten hacia mi, sea bueno o malo pero en vida, ya por muerta ¿para que??🤨
cómo seguidora del trabajo del llamado"kaiser" de la moda (emperador en alemán). es imposible olvidar lo controversial que fue cuando dijo que estaba harto del movimiento #metoo o cuando defendió a las modelos hiper delgadas o lo exigente que era con sus 100 dispositivos electrónicos para que estuviesen actualizados con su música favorita, trabajo que para muchos suena raro, pero a mi me hubiese caído como anillo al dedo que me pagaran por algo que me gusta, se imaginan 🤣🤣 yo armándole sus #playlist a eso le agregamos su fuerte carácter, su temperamento de hierro, sus fuertes posiciones sobre la vida, como el mismo lo decía "yo sé que tan molesto, imposible y difícil de complacer puedo ser. no me recomiendo a mí mismo como huésped de nadie". pero con todo lo antes mencionado, como humano imperfecto,  karl lagerfeld será  uno de los grandes de la moda, que inició en la capital francesa trabajando como asistente de pierre balmain antes de trabajar para fendi y chloe en la década de 1960, luego director  de la firma francesa chanel desde 1983, también se desempeñó como director creativo de fendi , además de diseñar colecciones para su propia marca karl lagerfeld y  colaborar con la cadena h&m que en 2 días se agotó su colección. en lo personal creo que su muerte va a marca un antes y un después en el mundo de la moda. 👆play ▶️ al vídeo con más datos interesantes de uno de mis favoritos. aunque siempre me sentí sentenciada cuando decía “"piensa en rosa, pero no lo vistas". 😋 💗
karl gracias por tanta inspiración .
.
.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significan notly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
its #tunetuesday! 🎶
_
this song is so groovy. and it’s the perfect wosc anthem for this week. 
_
listen to it to invoke some smooth and sexy confidence within yourself. it’s a love song about someone whose broken up with their significant other: the ex-lover didn’t think they could make it, but look at them now 👀
_
this message isn’t just relevant in romantic relationships, but in entrepreneurship, business and dream chasing too 🏃🏾‍♀️🏃🏼‍♀️🏃🏿‍♀️🏃🏽‍♀️
_
this is for the negative nancy’s and those who tell you to get your head out of the clouds or be more realistic.
🙄
-
don’t give up on your dreams. one day (if you haven’t already) you’ll tell them “look at me now” 😋
.
.
.
.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
day 1 of gabv 2019 summit: to operate as conscious leaders we need to experience an inner disruption - to move beyond our fictions and see the reality of ourselves and the world. i was really moved to see our design exchange sessions dominated by young leaders. as inheriters of our future, we feel an urgency to mobilise quickly and take advantage of these opportunities to learn, network, and co-create. a few gems/snippets from conversations and speakers: labour is being brutalized by capitalism, where labour being the people... networks as a means to generate power and that we should use platforms (i.e. facebook) to take back power as people... "when a woman is in a violent situation, having a bank account is not going to make things better." ... fund those on the frontlines because they know the solutions with the biggest impact... the aid that we currently provide foreign countries is a demonstration that we have it wrong... issues are fundamentally interconnected, and we need to embody wholism in our approaches.

speakers & panalests: 
musimbi kanyoro, ceo global fund for women
tima kurdi, refugee advocate and author
nathan benson, the refugee hub
gillian barth, ceo care canada
ebony harper, the california endowment
paul lacerte, ceo moosehide campaign
lisa mensah, ceo opportunity finance network
kat taylor, ceo beneficial state bank

#bankingonvalues #gabv2019 #leadership #vancouver #vancity #cityhive #youngleaders #metoo #humanmigration #gratitude #growth #expansion

text:
gender pay gap reporting provides an opportunity to scrutinise existing models of pay. first and foremost, are you paying your people fairly? if not, why not? do you have a transparent pay structure?
reporting also enables you to assess how employees are valued. who in the organisation is receiving promotions and rewards, and at what value? do you have an equal representation of genders across all levels of your organisation? how is performance measured and rewarded? is there a structured and formal promotion process?

there are various ways in which you can improve the gender pay gap in your organisation. you just need an action plan, and one that is lived, breathed and monitored to ensure its effectiveness.

text: “daughter, your faith has healed you.” 2019 digital illustration. “they took his clothes.” christ, in the process of his crucifixion, experienced the shame and humiliation all too familiar to the many people who can say metoo but what follows the degradation jesus experiences at the hands of many men is new life.  in the 2017 #womensmarch march, the feminist movement found its own #resurrection.  i created this image of #jesus donning a #pussyhat because christ himself was a #feminist and though many like to say that “god doesn’t take sides,” the gospel makes it clear, over and over, that god stands with those whom are subjugated, those who are violated, and those who are treated unjustly.  what you have done to the least of these, you have done to #metoo  this piece is available at http://bit.ly/metoojesus #feministtheology #feministliberationtheology #liberationtheology #sidewound #yourfaithhasmadeyouwell #feministart #pussycap #womensmarch2017 #photoshop #wacomtablet #womenssuffrage #feminism #theleastofthese #glassceiling #imwithhim #love #womenempowerment #art #redbubble #love #yesallwomen  #digitalpainting #digitalillustration #contemporaryart #sociallyengagedart

text:
introducing our #awlcrwanda2019 speakers
-

yewande austin
-

from mtv to the historic rock and roll hall of fame, yewande’s @officialyewande socially charged music has taken center stage with musical icons from the black eyed peas to maroon 5, but it is her work as an award-winning lecturer, social activist and honorary u. s. cultural ambassador that has become her greatest achievement. -

today, this 2018 bmw “women of excellence”, 2018 africa-usa today magazine “humanitarian” and 2017 president barack obama lifetime achievement award honoree is recognized as an international expert in strategic diversity leadership, multidisciplinary education, social responsibility and youth development. -

under her capacity building consultancy, the global institute for diversity and change, ms. austin has been credited with improving the climate of nearly 5,000 academic institutions, government agencies and non-profit organizations through evidence-based strategies as an innovative educator, keynote speaker and social impact leader for 14 years. -

read full biography at https://awlo.org/awlc/speaker/yewande-austin/

text:
it isn’t surprising to witness publications and people wax poetic about #lagerfeld’s genius while they ignore his history of oppressive comments towards anyone who did not fit into his narrow esthetic of human existence. lagerfeld took pride in being a gatekeeper of an industry which has for a long time continued to perpetuate white supremacy and other forms of oppression. he claimed that he didn’t feel constrained by coco chanel’s legacy as a designer, but he certainly continued a legacy of a far-right europe and a diluted version of his predecessor’s role as nazi spy and sympathizer.

rather than separating the art from the artist, i think it is time that fashion come to terms with lagerfeld’s abhorrent comments — the first thing to do would be to admit that they exist and that commentary continues to be harmful and that the designer’s beliefs only affirmed the feelings and ideologies of millions who hate people whose bodies fall outside of the white supremacist, misogynistic, ableist norm.
in 2017, lagerfeld had no issue stating that syrian and muslim migrants weren’t welcome in europe and pushed a both islamophobic and frankly anti-semitic idea that, “one cannot — even if there are decades between them — kill millions of jews so you can bring millions of their worst enemies in their place.” this comment was made just days after neo-nazis and white nationalists gathered in poland for demonstrations against black and brown migrants, chanting “pure poland, white poland!” and “refugees get out!” throughout his career, lagerfeld was notoriously #misogynistic.  in a 2018 interview, lagerfeld stated that he was “fed up” with the #metoo movement and that what shocked him the most was “the starlets who have taken 20 years to remember what happened. not to mention the fact that there are no prosecution witnesses” — as if the problem was memory and as if there are usually witnesses to sexual assaults. he continues with, ““if you don’t want your pants pulled about, don’t become a model! join a nunnery, there’ll always be a place for you in the convent. they’re recruiting even!” https://wearyourvoicemag.com/culture/anti-condolences-karl-lagerfeld

text:
[이벤트] 💥2019 여성의 날💥을 기념해 <더뮤지컬>이 뮤지컬을 사랑하는 많은 여성 관객분들과 의미 있는 시간을 보내고자 특별 강좌를 마련했습니다. 이름하여 ‘뮤지컬 속 여성 돌아보기! (중고등학생 여러분 매우 환영
_
🗓일 시:  3월 9일(토) pm 6:00
📍장 소:  예술가의집 3층 다목적홀
💰수강료: 1만 원 ⠀⠀
_
신청 바로 가기 👉🏼 프로필 상단 링크 클릭 ⠀⠀
_
✔️ 강의 소개
공연계가 무대 안팎의 성평등을 이루기 위해 나아가야 할 방향은 무엇일까. 여성의 날을기념해 열리는 본 강의는 브로드웨이 뮤지컬 속남성 캐릭터와 여성 캐릭터가 어떻게 다른 차이를 갖는지 살펴보며 그동안 수동적이고 도구화된 존재로 그려져 온 여성상을 비판적인 시각에서 점검한다.
_
✔️ 강사 소개
극작가 겸 공연 칼럼니스트. 주요 작품에 <콩칠팔 새삼륙>과 <신과 함께 가라>가 있다. 최근 <더뮤지컬>에 ‘여성의 눈으로 본 2018 뮤지컬’, ‘브로드웨이와 웨스트엔드의 여성 창작자들’, ‘#metoo #withyou 그리고 musical’을 기고했다. 또한 네이버 올댓아트 필진으로 활동하고 있다.
_
#더뮤지컬
#여성의날
#특별강좌
#timesup 
#girlscandoanything

공연계가 무대 안팎의 성평등을 이루기 위해 나아가야 할 방향은 무엇일까. 여성의 날을기념해 열리는 본 강의는 브로드웨이 뮤지컬 속남성 캐릭터와 여성 캐릭터가 어떻게 다른 차이를 갖는지 살펴보며 그동안 수동적이고 도구화된 존재로 그려져 온 여성상을 비판적인 시각에서 점검한다.

text:
come i nostri ascoltatori sapranno io vivo in california, e a volte, per me e' difficile capire cosa sta succedendo a livello culturale in italia. ma da quando ho iniziato questa pagina instagram ed ho iniziato a seguire altre pagine in italiano ho iniziato a capire che ancora c'e' molta confusione su cosa vuole dire essere una femminista. come e' possibile che nel mezzo della cosiddetta fourth wave of feminism, nel mezza dell'era del #metoo in italia tante persone (uomini e donne) non abbiano neanche chiaro cosa sia il femminismo??? questo e' triste. 
la cosa positiva e' vedere che comunque ci sono tantissime voci (di uomini e donne) che tentano di fare luce nell'abisso di ignoranza! quindi ho deciso di unirmi al coro di queste bellissime voci e creare un post che spiega il perche' io sono femminista. e pure il fatto che non odio gli uomini, che dovrebbe essere scontato ma aime' non lo e'. io ho tantissimi amici e colleghi uomini che rispetto, ammiro e a cui voglio un bene infinito. e questo non c'entra nulla con l'essere femminista, che e' il volere uguali diritti e opportunità per le donne. -elide

text:
ada lovelace, recognized as the world’s first computer programmer. her mentor was charles babbage, who invented a mechanical computer, dubbed the analytical engine. considered an early version of a calculator, ada looked at the device and found a way to improve it. she reasoned that if it could manipulate number to solve equations, it could do the same with symbols and be instructed to do almost anything. ada lovelace programmed the analytical engine to create music and graphics. she wrote a detailed description of how it could calculate an important series of numbers called bernoulli numbers.

-soms voelt het alsof ik in het niets sta-
weinig mensen kennen mij boos. maar het is de onmacht, het verdriet wat er elke keer weer uitkomt. elke keer dat ik opnieuw het verhaal van een iemand hoor die weet hoe het is. hoe het is om te leven na seksueel geweld.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
het voelt alsof je met de kraan open staat te dweilen. ik zou zo graag willen dat het anders was, dat er geen nieuwe verhalen meer bijkomen. dat het stopt. maar de realiteit is kneiterhard. ik kan het niet stoppen. het enige wat ik kan doen is het taboe doorbreken en mijn deur openzetten. jouw verhaal mag er zijn.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
al voelt het alsof ik in het niets sta, weet ik dat mijn verhaal er toe doet. weet ik dat ik niet alleen sta en dat meer mensen het anders willen. al voelt het soms alsof ik in het niets sta, ik weet dat ik niet alleen sta. ook als dat soms wel zo voelt.
